description: Lists blueprint configurations for a Amazon DataZone environment.

parameters.name: domainIdentifier
parameters.description: The identifier of the Amazon DataZone domain.

nested_items.name: items
nested_items.description: The results of the ListEnvironmentBlueprintConfigurations action.

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: The timestamp of when an environment blueprint was created.

nested_items.name: domainId
nested_items.description: The identifier of the Amazon DataZone domain in which an environment blueprint exists.

nested_items.name: enabledRegions
nested_items.description: The enabled Amazon Web Services Regions specified in a blueprint configuration.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: environmentBlueprintId
nested_items.description: The identifier of the environment blueprint.

nested_items.name: environmentRolePermissionBoundary
nested_items.description: The environment role permission boundary.

nested_items.name: manageAccessRoleArn
nested_items.description: The ARN of the manage access role specified in the environment blueprint configuration.

nested_items.name: provisioningConfigurations
nested_items.description: The provisioning configuration of a blueprint.

nested_items.name: lakeFormationConfiguration
nested_items.description: The Lake Formation configuration of the Data Lake blueprint.

nested_items.name: locationRegistrationExcludeS3Locations
nested_items.description: Specifies certain Amazon S3 locations if you do not want Amazon DataZone to automatically register them in hybrid mode.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: locationRegistrationRole
nested_items.description: The role that is used to manage read/write access to the chosen Amazon S3 bucket(s) for Data Lake using Amazon Web Services Lake Formation hybrid access mode.

nested_items.name: provisioningRoleArn
nested_items.description: The ARN of the provisioning role specified in the environment blueprint configuration.

nested_items.name: regionalParameters
nested_items.description: The regional parameters of the environment blueprint.
(string) ---
(string) ---
(string) ---

nested_items.name: updatedAt
nested_items.description: The timestamp of when the environment blueprint was updated.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: When the number of blueprint configurations is greater than the default value for the MaxResults parameter, or if you explicitly specify a value for MaxResults that is less than the number of configurations, the response includes a pagination token named NextToken. You can specify this NextToken value in a subsequent call to ListEnvironmentBlueprintConfigurations to list the next set of configurations.
